<subSubSection id="94A154849A024344FF57C8BBFCDF35B7" pageId="6" pageNumber="1241" type="description">
<paragraph id="DC04070F9A024344FF57C8BBFCDF35B7" blockId="6.[178,1085,1454,1535]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1241">
C o m m e n t: This winged species is apparently very rare. Previouly, only 
<specimenCount id="CABDCC869A024344FBF6C8BBFEDD35AA" pageId="6" pageNumber="1241" type="generic">four specimens</specimenCount>
from four localities in 
<collectingRegion id="1E7FC9ED9A024344FDC9C8D9FDBA35A9" box="[556,636,1484,1505]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="6" pageNumber="1241">Yunnan</collectingRegion>
(one of them unspecified) and southern 
<collectingRegion id="1E7FC9ED9A024344FF57C8FCFEC235B7" box="[178,260,1513,1535]" country="China" name="Sichuan" pageId="6" pageNumber="1241">Sichuan</collectingRegion>
were known (
<bibRefCitation id="B82A7AFE9A024344FE71C8FCFDEE35B6" author="ASSING V" box="[404,552,1513,1534]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1241" pagination="3 - 96" refId="ref6977" refString="ASSING V. (1999 a): A revision of Othius STEPHENS, 1829. VII. The species of the Eastern Palaearctic region east of the Himalayas (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae). - Beitrage zur Entomologie, Berlin 49 (1): 3 - 96." type="journal article" year="1999">ASSING 1999a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="B82A7AFE9A024344FDD7C8FCFDB235B7" author="ASSING V" box="[562,628,1513,1535]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1241" pagination="661 - 691" refId="ref7027" refString="ASSING V. (1999 b): A revision of Othius STEPHENS (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae). VIII. Further records, new species, and a new synonym. - Linzer Biologische Beitrage 31 (2): 661 - 691." type="journal article" year="1999">1999b</bibRefCitation>
